The signing ceremony was also attended by the Director General of the Turkish Red Crescent Society, Dr. Mohammad Guloglu, and the Coordinator of Ground Operations at the Association Kader Akinduz

The agreement was signed by the Turkish President, Dr. Abdullah Al-Maatouq, and by the Turkish Red Crescent President Dr. Karim Kenek. The visit was attended by Kuwaiti Ambassador to Ankara Ghassan Al-Zawawi, Director General Bader Al-Sumait, International Relations Advisor Hadeel Al-Sabti and Diplomatic Attach√© Habib Al-Duweila.

The International Islamic Charitable Society of Kuwait and the Turkish Red Crescent Society signed Friday a memorandum of understanding to achieve strategic partnership in helping vulnerable and disadvantaged groups around the world.
